This paper proposes a new deep reinforcement learning algorithm that is robust to partially observed state. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on reinforcement learning, it is less likely to belong to the sub-category of natural language processing. Among the remaining four sub-categories, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely one since the paper proposes a new deep reinforcement learning algorithm. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) are also likely since the paper deals with challenging domains and navigation benchmarks. Computer vision (cs.CV) is also a possible sub-category since the paper mentions learning control strategies from raw image pixels.
